#!/usr/bin/env python3
#
# ai-distill — distillation stage of the harvest pipeline. The deterministic
# bookends of the hybrid design (docs/ai-pipeline-threat-model.md §7); the
# inference middle (stages 4–8) runs as a human-supervised agent session (the
# `distill` plugin), between these two subcommands. Deployed by setup; do not
# edit — edit setup's source (files/ai-distill) instead.
#
#   ai-distill prepare [run-dir]   — reqs 1–3: read the newest catalog, select
#       refinement:derived, re-verify each sha256 and EXCLUDE mismatches (R2),
#       sanitize (canonicalize, opacity-unwrap, score, validate; §7 req 3),
#       exact-deduplicate, and emit a work package. Also open a quarantine pen
#       and create the primary worktree — a linked git worktree of the
#       workspace repo on branch distill/<run>, off the live path, where the
#       session writes the distilled ai/ directly.
#   ai-distill gate [run-dir] [target]   — run the deterministic checks on a
#       target's branch diff (added lines: no secrets, no executable config,
#       and for the hub no un-redacted identifiers; changed files must be ai/
#       prose, or non-config for a target repo). No proposal, no REVIEW.md —
#       git diff is the review artifact.
#   ai-distill apply [run-dir] [target]  — re-gate, then merge the reviewed
#       distill/<run> branch into the repo's live branch (the live tree, which
#       the tools read, updates at once) and REMOVE the worktree and branch —
#       no loose copy left behind.
#   ai-distill discard [run-dir] [target]  — drop a worktree and its branch
#       unapplied (a rejected proposal).
#   ai-distill add-target <run-dir> <repo> — open a worktree for a
#       suggest-to-repo target repo (the side channel), gated/applied the same
#       way as the workspace hub, except its own identifiers are allowed.
#
# Workflow: prepare → the session edits <worktree>/ai/ directly and commits →
# gate → the operator reviews `git diff` and iterates → apply merges into the
# live tree and cleans up. The session never freehand-edits the LIVE ai/ (the
# write-guard hook blocks it); only apply's merge mutates the live tree, on a
# reviewed branch. Quarantined items stay in the run's quarantine pen, outside
# every repo, until the operator rescues a false alarm into the worktree.
#
# No network, no model calls, no credentials. Only file: URLs are read; any
# other scheme is listed, never fetched (§7 req 2). Content is read only to
# sanitize and hash it. Uses only the standard library (system python3, 3.9+).

